'''Ambrose Mandvulo Dlamini''' (5 March 1968) is a [[Eswatini|Swazi]] [[business executive]] and the tenth [[List of Prime Ministers of Eswatini|Prime Minister of Eswatini]]. Prior to his appointment, he served as the [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of [[MTN Swaziland|Swazi MTN]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kozpost.com/blog/the-king-of-the-eswatini-appoints-a-prime-minister-a-novice-in-politics/13580/|title=The king of the eSwatini appoints a Prime minister, a novice in politics |website=Kozpost.com|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref>

==Prime Minister of Eswatini==
On October 27, 2018, King [[Mswati III]] announced in a gathering at the royal kraal at [[Lobamba]] that Dlamini would be the country’s next Prime Minister, to succeed [[Barnabas Sibusiso Dlamini]] who passed away the previous month, after the [[Swazi general election, 2018|2018 elections]]. Dlamini has no prior experience in politics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sabcnews.com/sabcnews/mandvulo-dlamini-appointed-eswatini-prime-minister/|title=Mandvulo Dlamini appointed eSwatini Prime Minister|website=Sabcnews.com|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://new.observer.org.sz/details.php?id=7171/|title=AMBROSE DLAMINI IS PRIME MINISTER|website=New.observer.org.sz|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref>

