'''Francis Parry''' [[F.R.G.S.]] was a British businessman in China and member of the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong]].

Parry was a member of the Birley & Co. He was elected as Trustees for the Year 1865–66, 1866–67, 1867–68 by the Seatholders of the [[St. John's Cathedral, Hong Kong]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunzi.lib.hku.hk/hkgro/view/g1865/714875.pdf|title=The Hongkong Government Gazette|date=29 April 1865|page=222|number=69}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunzi.lib.hku.hk/hkgro/view/g1866/713066.pdf|title=The Hongkong Government Gazette|date=5 May 1866|page=182|number=67}}</ref> He was appointed member of the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council]] vice [[Hugh Bold Gibb]]'s absence on leave in July 1867.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunzi.lib.hku.hk/hkgro/view/g1867/711758.pdf|title=The Hongkong Government Gazette|date=20 July 1867|number=112}}</ref>

He married to Jane, widow of Rev. James Gwynne, Rector of Cork, and daughter of the late Charles Osburn, [[Fareham]], [[Hampshire]].

