{{About|the CNBC program|the Fox Network comedy show|The Edge (Fox TV series)|the Fox News Channel program|The Edge (Fox News TV program)}} {{lead too short|reason=This article's lead only mentions the CNBC World version, but seems primarily focused on the original 1997 CNBC version.|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox television | show_name = The Edge | image = | caption = | camera = | picture_format = | audio_format = | runtime = | creator = | developer = | producer = | executive_producer = | presenter = {{Plainlist| * [[Sue Herera]] * [[Bill Griffeth]] * [[Ted David]] * Tom Mackenzie * [[Seema Mody]] }} | voices = | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | country = [[UK]] | location = | language = [[English language|English]] | network = [[CNBC]] | first_aired = {{Start date|1997|10|6}} | last_aired = present | num_series = | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | preceded_by = ''[[Business Tonight]]'' & ''[[Bull Session]]'' | followed_by = | related = | website = }}
'''''The Edge''''' is a primetime technology news television program produced by [[CNBC World]] that premiere in 1996 on [[CNBC]]. CNBC says ''The Edge'' targets long-term investors seeking emerging trends in technology and innovation. The half-hour monthly show is made-up of 3 or 4 feature length stories detailing new products, research, and predictions from industry analysts and business leaders.
==History== *''The Edge'' was originally a half-hour program produced by [[CNBC]] U.S. to replace ''[[Business Tonight]]'' in c. 1998, aired from 6:30 to 7pm ET. *In c. 1999, it was expanded to one hour, aired from 6 to 7. *In c. 2000, it was shortened to half-hour again, aired from 6 to 6:30. *In c. 2001, it was moved to 7:30 to 8pm timeslot, and ended its run. *In c. 2013, it was relaunched on [[CNBC World]], CNBC's sister channel. Production moved to [[CNBC World]]'s fleet place offices in [[London]] UK.
==''The Edge'' anchors== *[[Sue Herera]] (1997–1999) *[[Bill Griffeth]] (1999–March 2000) *[[Ted David]] (March 2000–February 2002) *Tom Mackenzie (August 2013–September 2014; CNBC World) *[[Seema Mody]] (November 2014–present; CNBC World)
